CHAPTER 2
PARTICIPANTS
See Rules

#rule("4", "TEAMS")[
]

#subrule("4.1", "TEAM COMPOSITION")[
]
  #r("4.1.1")[A team is composed exclusively of two players.]
  #r("4.1.2")[Only the two players recorded on the score sheet have the right to participate in the match.]
  #r("4.1.3")[One of the players is the team captain who shall be indicated on the score sheet.]
  #r("4.1.4")[For FIVB, World and Official Competitions, players are not allowed to receive external assistance or coaching during a match (Exceptions: see Specific Regulations for Age Competitions and for Phases 1 and 2 of the Continental Cup).]

#subrule("4.2", "LOCATION OF THE TEAM")[
  The team’s areas (including two chairs each) must be 5 m from the
  sideline, and no closer than 3 m from the scorer’s table.
]

#subrule("4.3", "EQUIPMENT")[
  A player’s equipment consists of shorts or a bathing suit. A jersey
  or “tank-top” is optional except when specified in Tournament
  Regulations. Players may wear a hat/head covering.
  4.1.1
]
  #r("4.3.1")[For FIVB, World and Official Competitions, players of a given team must wear uniforms of the same colour and style according to tournament regulations. Player’s uniforms must be clean.]
  #r("4.3.2")[Players must play barefoot except when authorized by the 1st referee.]
  #r("4.3.3")[Players’ jerseys (or shorts if players are allowed to play without shirt) must be numbered 1 and 2.]
  #r("4.3.3.1")[The number must be placed on the chest (or on the front of the shorts).]
  #r("4.3.3.2")[The number must be of a contrasting colour to the jersey and a minimum of 10 cm in height. The stripe forming the number shall be a minimum of 1.5 cm wide.]

#subrule("4.4", "CHANGE OF EQUIPMENT")[
  If both teams arrive at a match dressed in jerseys of the same colour, a
  toss shall be conducted to determine which team shall change.
  The first referee may authorize one or more players:
]
  #r("4.4.1")[to play with socks and/or shoes,]
  #r("4.4.2")[to change wet jerseys between sets provided that the new ones also follow tournament and FIVB regulations. 4.3.3]
  #r("4.4.3")[If requested by a player, the first referee may authorize him/her to play with an undershirt and training pants.]

#subrule("4.5", "FORBIDDEN OBJECTS")[
]
  #r("4.5.1")[It is forbidden to wear objects which may cause injury or give an artificial advantage to the player.]
  #r("4.5.2")[Players may wear glasses or lenses at their own risk.]
  #r("4.5.3")[Compression pads (padded injury protection devices) may be worn for protection or support. For FIVB, World and Official Competitions for seniors, these devices or visible underwear must be of the same colour as part of the uniform. Black, white or neutral colours may be also used provided that all using players wear the same colour.]

#rule("5", "TEAM LEADERS")[
  The team captain is responsible for maintaining team conduct and discipline.
]

#subrule("5.1", "CAPTAIN")[
]
  #r("5.1.1")[PRIOR TO THE MATCH, the team captain: a) Signs the score sheet. b) Represents his/her team in the toss.]
  #r("5.1.2")[During the match, only the captain is authorized to speak to the referees while the ball is out of play in the following three cases: 8.2]
  #r("5.1.2.1")[to ask for an explanation on the application or interpretation of the Rules; if the explanation does not satisfy the captain, the captain must immediately inform the 1st referee of his/her wish to Protest;]
  #r("5.1.2.2")[to ask authorization: a) to change uniforms or equipment, b) to verify the number of the serving player, c) to check the net, the ball, the surface etc., d) to realign a court line;]
  #r("5.1.2.3")[to request time-outs. 15.2.1, 15.4.1 Note: the players must have authorization from the referees to leave the playing area.]
  #r("5.1.3")[AT THE END OF THE MATCH:]
  #r("5.1.3.1")[Both players thank the referees and the opponents. The Captain signs the score sheet to ratify the result;]
  #r("5.1.3.2")[If the captain previously requested a Protest Protocol via the 1 st referee and this has not been successfully resolved at the time of the occurrence, he/she has the right to confirm it as a formal written protest, recorded on the score sheet at the end of the match. 5.1.2.1]
